# Launcher panel chrome (frozen)

Read **`docs/specs/LAUNCHER_PANEL_CONSTRAINTS.md`** before changing panel size, placement, show animation, presentation screen, or in-panel layout.  
Navigation / shortcuts: **`docs/specs/UX_BEHAVIOR_RULES.md`** + **`docs/qa/LAUNCHER_NAVIGATION_AUDIT.md`**.

## Geometry

- Default **940 × 760 pt**, upper-third (`panelVerticalBias` 0.68); empty home left column **360 pt** (ADR-032).
- Math lives in `LauncherPanelGeometry.swift`; `LauncherPanel.position(on:)` is the only placement API.

## Positioning — do NOT

- Set `anchorPoint` or scale transforms on the panel `contentView` layer.
- Split `setContentSize` and `setFrameOrigin` without re-centering.
- Use `window.center()` for Settings on multi-monitor setups.
- Resize the panel from detail content width.

## Positioning — always

- `LumaPresentationScreen.current()` then `panel.position(on: visibleFrame)` on every show.
- Atomic `setFrame`; lock `minSize`/`maxSize` after position.
- Alpha fade only for show/hide — no scale animation.
- Call `LauncherInPanelLayout.stabilizePanel(from:)` after search, results, home, and detail layout changes.
- `LauncherPanel.enforceLockedGeometry()` clamps drifted width/height to `lockedFrameSize` and re-centers.

## In-panel layout — do NOT

- `wantsLayer = true` on full-width hosts: root view, `contentContainer`, `detailContainer`, list row host, `BaseDetailContainer` root, custom detail root.
- Glass/border/shadow/selection directly on those hosts.

## In-panel layout — always

- Fixed panel width; detail views scroll or truncate — never widen the panel.
- Empty-query home: module detail in **right column** only (`LauncherHomeSplitLayout`); left Open Apps stay visible.
- Put chrome on **pinned child views** (`GeekUIKit.installSearchSurface`, `configureContentSurface`, `installHomeListSurface`, list row `backgroundView`, `LauncherActionPanel.chromeView`).
- Custom details: pin stacks to `container.leading`/`trailing` or `container.widthAnchor`; crowded toolbars use `constrainDetailToolbarTrailingActions`.
- Disable mouse hits on fading `detailContainer` / `listView` during cross-fade (audit L1).
- Module detail placeholders: `L10n.tr` with string literals.
- Bounded widgets (icons, keycaps, table rows, thumbnails) may use `wantsLayer` on the widget only.

## PR requirements

Update `LAUNCHER_PANEL_CONSTRAINTS.md`, `UX_BEHAVIOR_RULES.md`, and `MANUAL_QA_CHECKLIST.md` when panel or in-panel layout rules change.
